\par An }{\fs20\cf0\super M}{\fs12\cf0  }{\fs20\cf0 or }{\fs20\cf0\super F}{\fs12\cf0  }{\fs20\cf0 appearing at the end of a spell\rquote s name in the spell lists denotes a spell with a material or focus component, respect
ively, that is not normally included in a spell component pouch. An }{\fs20\cf0\super X}{\fs12\cf0  }{\fs20\cf0 denotes a spell with an XP component paid by the caster.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Order of Presentation: }{\fs20\cf0 In the spell lists and the spell descriptions that follow them, the spells are presented in alphabetical order by name except for those belonging to certain spell chains.
\par When a spell\rquote s name begins with \'93lesser,\'94 \'93greater,\'94 or \'93mass,\'94 the spell description is alphabetized under the second word of the spell name instead.}{\i\fs20\cf0 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Hit Dice: }{\fs20\cf0 The term \'93Hit Dice\'94 is used synonymously with \'93character levels\'94
 for effects that affect a number of Hit Dice of creatures. Creatures with Hit Dice only from their race, not from classes, have character levels equal to their Hit Dice.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Caster Level:}{\fs20\cf0  A spell\rquote s power often depends on caster level, which is defined as the caster\rquote 
s class level for the purpose of casting a particular spell. A creature with no classes has a caster level equal to its Hit Dice unless otherwise specified. The word \'93level\'94 in the spell lists that follow always refers to caster level.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Creatures and Characters: }{\fs20\cf0 The words \'93creature\'94 and \'93character\'94 are used synonymously in the spell descriptions.
